We use 416R stainless steel and our rifling shape is a series of arcs instead of square corners, as in the traditional style of Enfield rifling. This arc shaped rifling has long been held in very high regard for its accuracy, increased velocity, reduced gas cutting and ease of cleaning. Here you can see the difference between classic Enfield rifling compared to the 5 land and 3 land polygonal rifling.
Product Development and testing We use steel from one of the nations largest steel suppliers.We have an ongoing inspection process as a proactive quality control measure on our products. We are trying to raise enough money to really buy a spot in the supply chain for this area in colorado and surrounding. We have access to and some stock of mostly anything you would want and can likely sell it to you cheaper than a retail outlet could.

We will not however be underselling our local gun stores as they are just as important to our rights as this company.

We have connections set up for helping you with gun parts and reloading components at prices lower than most and if you are local, no shipping.

We are offering the chance for regular people to help build a real munitions company, with the end goal of having the ability to make ALL of our own components and even to include rimfire ammo.

At this point a crowdfunding effort is necessary to achieve our goals before we the people are regulated out of this industry altogether. Together we in Colorado can ensure we are not ever again subject to shortages and the like. This will take work and time, but my fancy clubs are worth feeding, aren't yours??

Please join us on our journey to freedom, via rewards based or equity based crowdfunding. Yes you can end up owning part of a munitions company. This can pay in money or ammo(is there a difference?)

Thanks to all for your support already, we have been here as a family since the start, proudly fighting, and would be honored to have you with us!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger P97 DC Stainless .45 ACP UPGRADED w spare mags and parts
postcontent:
This is the classic Ruger P97 DC (Decocker) .45 ACP. It has Williams Gun Sight adjustable fiber optic sights. Even though the pistol has had only light range use I had everthing refit to max out the pistols performance. All springs have been replaced in pistol and magazines. Reduced hammer spring to lighten the DA trigger pull, increased recoil spring to tame the felt recoil and limit wear and tear on the frame. and a 5% increase for all the new magazine springs to insure proper feeding. Friction points and feed ramp have been lightly polished. It also has a Houge/Ruger wrap around grip. Only very light scuffing can be found on the fiberglass filled urethane frame, everything else is 100%.

This pistol is very accurate and reliable... While it's a bit bulky it beats out most 1911s. Feeds anything very well, from 180 to 230 FMJ and HP, it seems to have no issues with even the widest mouth hollow points. It has a very smooth DA trigger pull with no creep that runs about 8lbs, the SA trigger breaks at roughly 3.5lbs with very little pre travel. The adjustable Williams Gunsight (of Davidson Mi) fiber optic sights catch just the right amount of light indoors or outdoor. 

Package also included rare and sometimes difficult to find spare parts.

Package includes
Sturm, Ruger P97 DC Stainless .45 ACP with 4.2" barrel
Six 8 round magazines with new +5% springs and S&R floor plates
Spare springs, sears, and barrel
Factory original iron sights (white 3 dot)
Ruger factory case

For full specs and info goto 
http://hunting.about.com/od/guns/l/aastrugerp97a.htm
